[src:secure-boot-chain/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] Intel's implementation of EFI is the *Intel Platform Innovation Framework*, codenamed *Tiano*.
[src:secure-boot-chain/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] Tiano runs on Intel's XScale, Itanium, IA-32 and x86-64 processors, and is proprietary software, although a portion of the code has been released under the BSD license or Eclipse Public License (EPL) as TianoCore EDK II.
